{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"isi9qi80jvtfqv94g6cmv93","title":"Universal Particles","desc":"","updated":1675371902367,"created":1675370016654,"custom":{},"fname":"Computer Graphics.Universal Particles","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"49256ddbaf3319620867037f323ab36e","links":[{"from":{"fname":"Computer Graphics.Position Based System","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":3,"offset":146},"end":{"line":4,"column":44,"offset":187},"indent":[]},"value":"Computer Graphics.universal particles","alias":"Computer Graphics.universal particles"},{"from":{"fname":"Chores.journal.2023.02.02","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":9,"offset":512},"end":{"line":5,"column":50,"offset":553},"indent":[]},"value":"Computer Graphics.universal particles","alias":"Computer Graphics.universal particles"}],"anchors":{"pbd---position-based-dynamics":{"type":"header","text":"PBD - Position Based Dynamics","value":"pbd---position-based-dynamics","line":10,"column":0,"depth":3},"rigid-body---rigid-shape-matching":{"type":"header","text":"Rigid Body - Rigid Shape matching","value":"rigid-body---rigid-shape-matching","line":13,"column":0,"depth":3},"sdf---signed-distance-field":{"type":"header","text":"SDF - Signed Distance Field","value":"sdf---signed-distance-field","line":19,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"xchs0m15uo5tnn2psd6a2ct","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"universal-particles\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#universal-particles\"></a>Universal Particles</h1>\n<p>Basically, it is \"a unified solver capable of simulating gases, liquids, deformable solids, rigid bodies, and cloth, interacting with one another in real-time.\"</p>\n<h3 id=\"pbd---position-based-dynamics\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#pbd---position-based-dynamics\"></a>PBD - <a href=\"https://matthias-research.github.io/pages/publications/posBasedDyn.pdf\">Position Based Dynamics</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Typically positions are updated after each constraint is processed, and after a number of iterations a change in velocity is computed according to the total constraint delta: delta_x = delta_x/delta_t.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"rigid-body---rigid-shape-matching\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#rigid-body---rigid-shape-matching\"></a>Rigid Body - <a href=\"https://matthias-research.github.io/pages/publications/orientedParticles.pdf\">Rigid Shape matching</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Shapes are created by first performing solid voxelization of a closed triangle mesh and placing particles at occupied cells interior to the shape. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Assign all particles in the shape the same phase-identifier, disable collision between them, and add a shape-matching constraint to the system.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"sdf---signed-distance-field\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#sdf---signed-distance-field\"></a>SDF - Signed Distance Field</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Sample the field function onto each particle belonging to a rigid shape. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Re-use all the machinery of the particle-particle collision detection to resolve deeper overlaps between shapes. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>detect overlaps between particles with distance <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>j</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">|xi − xj | &#x3C; r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span></span>. As the contact normal we choose the SDF gradient corresponding to the minimum translation distance, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>φ</mi><mi>i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>φ</mi><mi>j</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">d = min(|φi|, |φj |)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">min</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>φ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">φ</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span></span></span></span></span> is the magnitude of the SDF.</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/dendron-blogs/notes/cziki8zxr177n1y8m0q9ki2\">Position Based System</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/dendron-blogs/notes/hhlt1oum2s23ebdyunm4qrf\">2023-02-02</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Cy Blogs","desc":"","updated":1675108925086,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"b2360726a7a5a6ea703247f869656a1c","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-cy-blog":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Cy Blog","value":"welcome-to-cy-blog","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["xchs0m15uo5tnn2psd6a2ct","e15sw2ol9d3xec39qk81p4z","c77uo335fzt81rmc69hw9x0","syfz4mn1awpil68zjqzw14z","wfsauow9ogy3grk51rx612p"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\n# Welcome to Cy Blog\n\n> This website is generated by a Dendron template. \n\nExplore with me!\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enableP